<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective, 
<emphasis box="[652,742,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">aeratus,</emphasis>
meaning “of copper, bronze, or brass”, in reference to the brassy colour of the tomentosity covering all parts of the head, especially the fronto-orbital plate and parafacial. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,223,248]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,484,223,248]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, ACG, Prov. Alajuela &amp; Guanacaste, rain forest, 
<quantity box="[1032,1159,224,248]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="510.0" valueMax="700.0" valueMin="320.0">320–700 m</quantity>
elevation.
</paragraph>
